text: The corner fish soup stall run by a middle age couple has very nice soup base. I usually have their seafood e-mee which is chock full of ingredients for only SGD 6. Prawns, fish slices, dumplings, fish cake, etc. Love the clear broth which is not too overpowering but sweet enough. Worth a try.
Their yuan yang - c is smooth, slightly thick, less sweet and comes with tea/coffee aroma. 9/10
Laksa(large size) is only $5..! Taste is not bad;)

This is not a restaurant- just a small old school local coffeeshop with chicken rice, fish ball noodle which is selling laksa as well, Chinese style economical rice, etc. alongside  the busy pasir panjang road with the west coast highway running parallel overhead. In between and near to pasir panjang mrt station and Labrador park mrt station.
Popular lunch venues for port workers located opposite Hillman 99, this is the only other venue other than Pasir Panjang Food Centre for port workers.
